gate: LOCKED
sprint: S04
track: B
task: B1
title: "test(catalog): nuqs throttled-queue timer fires after jsdom teardown (#1442)"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: P2
refs:
  - CROP-front#1442
requires: [TYPESCRIPT]

description: |
  The nuqs throttled-queue timer fires after jsdom has torn down, producing an
  unhandled ReferenceError that randomly fails unit tests. This is a test
  environment leak — the timer is not cleaned up before the test suite exits.
  Fix: ensure the throttled queue is flushed/cancelled in afterEach or by
  mocking the timer so it never fires asynchronously past test boundary.

scope:
  in:
    - Identify the test(s) affected (grep: nuqs, throttled, ReferenceError in test output)
    - Add afterEach cleanup: cancel/flush the nuqs queue or use fake timers
    - Confirm 10/10 deterministic runs with `bun test --repeat 10` (or equivalent)
  out:
    - Changing nuqs runtime behavior in production code
    - Any other flaky tests (separate issues)

acceptance:
  - Affected test file(s) pass 10/10 consecutive runs
  - No ReferenceError in CI output after fix

dep: none
output: affected test file(s) patched with cleanup
